# Copy to `.env.production` for local production builds, or set the same variable
# in CI / Render (Static Site → Environment) for deployed builds.
# SpacetimeDB on Render listens on 127.0.0.1 inside the container; browsers must use the public service URL (https → wss). See packages/server/README.md § Render deploy.
#
# When to set this:
# - **Split deploy:** `@zylem/examples` is built and hosted as a static site (or CDN) *separate* from the
#   Docker web service that runs SpacetimeDB — set `VITE_STDB_URI` to that service’s public https://… origin
#   (e.g. `https://zylem-spacetimedb.onrender.com`). Demos such as four-characters-plane use this for `wss://`.
# - **Same Docker image as SpacetimeDB:** omit `VITE_STDB_URI`; the client uses `window.location.origin`.
#
# Must be a full origin with hostname (https://…). Do NOT use a bare port (e.g. ws://10000 — that breaks in browsers).
VITE_STDB_URI=https://your-spacetimedb-service.onrender.com
